I just noticed the following post, posted some time ago on a different thread, and think it is relevant to us now:             Thu Sep 11 23:02:19 US/Eastern 1997 <br>
I have made many trips back to the Nam and in 92 i wrote in the guest book at Cu  Chi. toys and went home The local Vietnamese thought that was the truth. We could have taken over the country if the Leaders in DC would have let us. You can't fight a war with rules. It is do it or get out. You cant let it drag on like it was done in the Nam. The war would have ended if we invaded the north and it would have been all over in a few days. But hind sight is 20/20. <br>
                 Hoa Bien (Peace)<br>
                And WELCOME HOME BROTHERS AND SISTERS.<br>
                namvietAnhHung     -- (nam viet Anh Hung)<br><br>
